* When adding or subtracting polynomials, only combine like terms (same variable part and same exponent).
* When multiplying polynomials, every term in the first factor must be multiplied by every term in the second factor.
* The degree of a sum or difference cannot be determined without evaluating; it depends on the leading terms.
* The degree of a product is the sum of the degrees of the factors.
